<br>
The reason you didn't get rules is I was a bit busy plus the lappy is kinda hard to type on.<br>
<br>
Bring Cold resist and Fire resist gear. With buffs I'm over 200 in both and still take alot of A/E dmg. Try to reach 100 min unbuffed. Fire is more important then cold IMO because even with a much lower cr I was resisting alot of cold based. I'll try and get a list of easy to obtain items.<br>
<br>
As it stands right now 55 min lvl though I may (prolly) will allow 54 ally to CoV. Before I here any grumbling about this there are 2 reasons - 1. I've seen 54's be effective and I want stuff dead fast 2. We had to call the raid way early last time because of peeps leaving and we simply didn't have the numbers to continue. <br>
<br>
NO PETS. The only way a pet will be allowed is if you summon it AFTER we engage and kill it immediately after the fight. If I allow this and you do not follow those rules I will ask you to leave. So pet owners be prepared with lots of pet reagents.<br>
<br>
Dozekar the Cursed is on the menu. I've talked to some friends about killing him and have a strategy in mind. I'm told he can be slowed w/o even tashing. He'll be pulled early in the raid as early as poss and we will either sink or swim with him and then get back to farming armor. I am not sure on how I plan to random the tears, i'm told he drops anywhere from 2-8 at a time. The idea I'm leaning most towards is people who are done with SS armor get 2 numbers all others get 1. I'll think more on it and decide later. There is a complete (i think) list of the West wing quests up at my reference site <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.geocities.com/keylargo60634">www.geocities.com/keylargo60634</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
For those who are new to ToV/HoT:<br>
<br>
NEVER Open the door to HoT during a fight. The CoV aligned mobs will come in and kill us all. If you arrive late (please don't we need peeps on time to do Doze) you come to the door and ASK IF IT IS CLEAR!<br>
<br>
NEVER drag anyone's corpse but your own! If a corpse is in the pit someone exp in ToV dragging will handle it.<br>
<br>
Casters DO NOT sit closer then TWO LARGE tiles to the pit. <br>
<br>
The A/E in ToV is Line of Sight (LoS) based. You can hide around a corner from the mob and it will not hit you.<br>
<br>
There are more rules but for now with 1 cup of coffee it's all I can think of.<br>
<br>
<br>
Last piece rule is in effect.<br>
<br>
Another Idea I am thinking about I've seen another guild use and sounded like a good way to handle plate drops is class roll then peep roll. Plate has like 5 classes rolling on it and lots of peeps from those classes. The way the class roll works is when a piece of plate drops a random of the 5 plate classes is done (Bard 1 Cleric 2 Pal 3 SK 4 War 5) then whatever class roll wins those class peeps roll. As a class wins that class is knocked out until all classes are provided for. This is just a thought and I'd like peeps input on it. When you sign up if you are a Plate class give me your opinion (or be like Adjani and give me your opinion even though you're not plate class). I think it's a good idea but others may not so I'll decide on doing it based on peoples input.<br>
<br>
As Adja said ask me in regards to any exceptions of these rules.  <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub75.ezboard.com/utanisemanasponge.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tanise Manasponge</A> at: 8/30/01 8:42:47 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CAD5D8><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub75.ezboard.com/ualundraadjani.showPublicProfile?language=EN>AlundraAdjani</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Saucy Phantasmist</span><br>  Posts: 760<br> <font color=#333333>(8/28/01 2:27:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub75.ezboard.com/ftrk72095frm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=54.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://alundraadjani.com/otherstuff/eq/catface.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: HoT TrK-ES-SC Tuesday the 4th</span><hr size=1> Sigh, I ask Tanise to post the &quot;rules and stuff&quot; and this is what I get.<br>
