<br>
Well *somebody* has to set the dumb tanks straight. :P<br>
<br>
Anyhow, I don't like the plate classes rolling idea at all.  Let's say you're an SK, like nascens, and there is one of you on the raid.  If SKs win the roll, it's yours, then SKs are out for the rest of the raid.  Sounds good.  But let's say you're a cleric, like Lashanna.  Clerics win the roll, and someone else gets it, but clerics are STILL out until all other plate classes have won something.  It would give Nascens a 1 in 5 chance of winning something, but it would give Lash more like a 1 in 25 chance.  Then Nascens could feasibly win 2 pieces in one raid when other plate wears had not won anything (would not be unlikely with his luck either. :P).<br>
<br>
I think we should just roll the way we always have, random to all peeps who need the piece of armor then the winner is out till everyone else has won something. <p><img src="http://www.annastazia.homestead.com/files/adjani.jpg" alt="Adjani Tristesse, Goddess of Lanys"></img>
